      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/ee7513/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2024-01-26T14:49:07.717Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Wow \u2026 this is just one of the reasons why I am so grateful that I found Trainer Day after all those years with Trainer Road. Thank you <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/pray.png?v=9\" title=\":pray:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":pray:\"></p>\n<p>The app was very useable in the early days if not quite as slick as TR. However I have had the privilege to be able to enjoy the journey with you and appreciate just how innovative &amp; proactive you and your team are as the website &amp; app have evolved &amp; developed in so many ways at such a fast pace.</p>\n<p>Not only embracing what other softwares are offering but also leading the way with really useful users functions &amp; options. It really is the best cycling app for training and then the price makes it totally unbeatable.</p>\n<p>Really appreciate all of your dedication &amp; persistence as I know it can\u2019t have always been easy. No idea what else you will come up with but I look forward to sitting back and watching how the future unfolds.</p>\n<p>Thank you from one truly appreciative user.</p>\n<p>I will give the \u201cfix\u201d a try in the morning and I am sure everything will be just fine.</p>\n<p>Kind regards</p>\n<p>Karl.</p>",
